							<h5 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#61063B] dark:text-white mb-3 italic">"Decolonizing Knowledge Production: Action Research as a Pathway to Inclusive and Culturally Responsive Education"</h5>
							<div class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed text-justify">
								<p class="mb-4">
									This plenary presentation draws from my study <em>Postcolonial Conceptions, Practices, and Challenges of Action Research in Philippine Higher Education</em>, which examined how higher education faculty navigate the complex terrain of research, teaching, and community engagement. Using a postcolonial lens, the study reveals how action research (AR) functions as a contested site of knowledge production, where globally dominant models are adapted, resisted, and hybridized to fit local needs and priorities.
								</p>
								<p class="mb-4">
